-- Spain’s Diaz Says Deficit in 2011 May Reach 8.2%, Pais Says
-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 2012-01-03T06:52:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/spain-s-diaz-says-deficit-in-2011-may-reach-8-2-pais-says.html
Spanish Interior Minister Jorge Fernandez Diaz estimates that the country’s public deficit in
2011 may reach 8.2 percent of gross domestic product,  El Pais 
reported, citing Diaz.  Diaz made the comments yesterday after Economy Minister
Luis de Guindos said during a radio interview with Cadena Ser
that the deficit could exceed 8 percent of GDP, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
